│ In our case, `ValAssumedPoison` is `%cmp` (an FCmpInst). `canCreatePoison` for FCmpInst should return true because floating-point comparisons can create  │
│ poison when operands are poison.                                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                           │
│ So the function should return false, which means `impliesPoisonOrCond` should return false, and the transformation shouldn't happen.                      │
